4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT GENERALLY REVISING LAWS REGARDING DISCRIMINATORY
5 PRACTICES IN EDUCATION; PROVIDING THAT IT IS AN UNLAWFUL DISCRIMINATORY PRACTICE FOR
6 AN EDUCATIONAL INSTITUTION TO ALLOW A MALE PERSON TO PARTICIPATE IN ATHLETIC
7 PROGRAMS DESIGNATED FOR FEMALE PERSONS; PROVIDING THAT IT IS AN UNLAWFUL
8 DISCRIMINATORY PRACTICE FOR AN EDUCATIONAL INSTITUTION TO FAIL TO PROVIDE A PERSON
9 WITH ACCESS TO A RESTROOM, LOCKER ROOM, SHOWER AREA, OR SLEEPING QUARTER THAT IS
10 INACCESSIBLE BY A PERSON OF THE OPPOSITE SEX WHILE IN USE; PROVIDING EXCEPTIONS; AND
11 AMENDING SECTION 49-2-307, MCA.”
12
13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
14
15 Section 1. Section 49-2-307, MCA, is amended to read:
16 "49-2-307. Discrimination in education. (1) It is an unlawful discriminatory practice for an
17 educational institution:
18 (a) to exclude, expel, limit, or otherwise discriminate against an individual seeking admission as a
19 student or an individual enrolled as a student in the terms, conditions, or privileges of the institution because of
20 race, creed, religion, sex, marital status, color, age, physical disability, or national origin or because of mental
21 disability, unless based on reasonable grounds;
22 (b) to make or use a written or oral inquiry or form of application for admission that elicits or
23 attempts to elicit information or to make or keep a record concerning the race, color, sex, marital status, age,
24 creed, religion, physical or mental disability, or national origin of an applicant for admission, except as permitted
25 by regulations of the commission;
26 (c) to print, publish, or cause to be printed or published a catalog or other notice or advertisement
27 indicating a limitation, specification, or discrimination based on the race, color, creed, religion, age, physical or
28 mental disability, sex, marital status, or national origin of an applicant for admission; or
